notesStmt.note: Folio 24r contains a narrative on Moses, probably inserted here by the scribe (not in other versions of the same treatise).
Two leaves, folio 156r-157v, are appended, containing fragments on the computation of various eras by Muhamad ibn Abi Bakr al-Farisi, written ca. 16th century.
The fly-leaf at the end, folio fse001r, contains a small part of the commentary of Rashi on the last chapter of Deuteronomy.
Afizi ben Shalom ben Yosef ben Zekharyah, writing for Se῾adyah ben Shalom, Daṿid ben Shalom and Yosef ben Shalom, inscribed in the colophon, folio 155v.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.
